H0.text: What is the name of the warm dry wind that blows on the est side of the Rocky Mountains in North America, usually in winter and spring. Chinookan

H1.text: What is the name of the warm dry wind that blows on the est side of the Rocky Mountains in North America, usually in winter and spring. Foehn Wind

H2.text: What is the name of the warm dry wind that blows on the est side of the Rocky Mountains in North America, usually in winter and spring. Sirocco

H3.text: What is the name of the warm dry wind that blows on the est side of the Rocky Mountains in North America, usually in winter and spring. C̓inúk

A4.text: In the North American western interior, winds that are generally called föhn winds by meteorologists and climatologists are called 'Chinooks'.

A5.text: The coastal Chinook winds deliver tremendous amounts of moisture both as rain along the coast and snow in the coastal mountains, that sustain the characteristic temperate rainforests and climate of the Pacific Northwest.
